      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T10:50:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Issue: Incomplete synchronization — reads bypass the lock. executeRequest() holds synchronized(queue) / synchronized(map) while writing, but channelRead0() calls\n    queue.poll() / map.remove() and channelInactive() drains both collections without holding the same lock. This makes the critical section ineffective and leaves\n    TOCTOU windows open.\n  Severity: Major\n  Recommendation: Either (a) remove synchronized and rely solely on the concurrent collection\u0027s own guarantees (simpler and was the original intent, given the\n    ConcurrentLinkedQueue/ConcurrentHashMap choices), or (b) add the same synchronized block around all accesses including channelRead0 and channelInactive. Option (a)\n    is cleaner.",
      "revId": "10e1de33a5f3b035eb140121344ec336a0b9ff84",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
