      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T10:50:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Issue: Race between invoke() and channelInactive(). A caller can pass the channel !\u003d null guard in invoke(), then be preempted. channelInactive() runs, calls\n    clearChannel(), drains the collection, and returns. The original caller resumes, enters executeRequest(), and adds its callback to the (now-empty) collection. That\n    callback will never receive onFailure.\n  Severity: Major\n  Recommendation: The safest fix is to hold a single lock that guards both the channel reference and the collection mutation. E.g., in invoke(): acquire the lock,\n    snapshot the channel, add to collection, write — all under one lock; channelInactive() acquires the same lock, nulls the channel, drains.",
      "revId": "10e1de33a5f3b035eb140121344ec336a0b9ff84",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    }
